## Public Member Functions

### filter() {#ae17194d7c43b1fa4e468363cb9473021}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void MarkupFilter::filter (std::string &amp;&amp; InputLine)</>}>
Filters a line containing symbolizer markup and writes the human-readable results to the output stream.

Invalid or unimplemented markup elements are removed. Some output may be deferred until future <a href="#ae17194d7c43b1fa4e468363cb9473021">filter()</a> or <a href="#ae4d58be2ab3e5166ba5447ed90271d8a">finish()</a> call.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/symbolize/markupfilter-h/#l00042">42</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/symbolize/markupfilter-h">MarkupFilter.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/symbolize/markupfilter-cpp/#l00041">41</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/symbolize/markupfilter-cpp">MarkupFilter.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
